FunboxEasyEnum

Target IP: 192.168.167.132

Scanning



There are only two ports open on the target machine: SSH and HTTP.

Enumeration

Port 80: HTTP

Performing a nikto scan shows there are interesting directories like the robots.txt and phpmyadmin. Browsing to /robots.txt outputs an entry called Enum_this_Box. However, this directory does not exist! But the phpmyadmin does!


Running a directory search using gobuster shows an interesting php page called mini.php.


Browsing to mini.php shows the webpage above. It looks like a web shell that has been uploaded. We have the ability to upload files using this web shell!


To test this, I uploaded a test.txt file with the content hi! and it worked as I was able to access it! It looks like all files are directly uploaded to /var/www/html directory, so we can access it by http://192.168.167.132/<filename>. Time to upload a reverse shell and get a connection from the target machine!

Exploitation


To exploit the machine, I created a file called shell_evil.php. This file contained the PHP PentestMonkey reverse shell script. After changing the IP and port parameters to point to my machine, I uploaded the script using the mini.php web shell, started a listener on port 8443, and browsed to http://192.168.167.132/shell_evil.php to activate it! And then I gained a foothold on the machine ad www-data!

Privilege Escalation


I found the password hash of the user oracle after running cat /etc/passwd! This hash is in md5crypt format. I stored this password hash in a file called hash.


I cracked the password of oracle using hashcat. I ran the command hashcat -m 500 hash /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt. and obtained the password hiphop.


And this worked. I am now oracle.


After some enumeration, I found the PHP file with the username and password. It is phpmyadmin:tgbzhnujm!. I was unable to read this file as oracle, but I could as www-data. And spraying this password against all the users did not work except karla.


Spraying the password above worked and now I am root!
